# to live a [[carefree]] life with very little material means; to [[live on bread and kisses]]
#: {{ux|fr|On ne peut pas '''vivre d’amour et d’eau fraiche'''.|You can't '''live off love and water alone'''. (The implication is that you need to work to earn a living.)}}
#: {{ux|fr|Sommes-nous revenus au temps où l'artiste était tenu de '''vivre d'amour et d'eau fraîche''' ? À l'évidence oui !|Have we returned to the times in which an artist had to '''live off love and water alone'''? Apparently so!}}

====Usage notes====
The expression emphasizes the unsustainability of the lifestyle. It is often used in the negative to chide children.

